#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an5.88"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an5.88:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 5 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 5 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.88:0.2"
msgid "9. Theravagga "
msgstr "9. Senior Mendicants "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an5.88:0.3"
msgid "88. Therasutta "
msgstr "88. Senior Mendicants "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "an5.88:1.1"
msgid "“Pañcahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato thero bhikkhu bahujanaahitāya paṭipanno hoti bahujanaasukhāya bahuno janassa anatthāya ahitāya dukkhāya devamanussānaṃ. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, a senior mendicant who has five qualities is acting for the hurt and unhappiness of the people, for the harm, hurt, and suffering of gods and humans. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.115, sc2
msgctxt "an5.88:2.1"
msgid "Katamehi pañcahi? "
msgstr "What five? "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.88:2.2"
msgid "Thero hoti rattaññū cirapabbajito; "
msgstr "They are senior and have long gone forth. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: sagahaṭṭhapabbajitānaṃ → gahaṭṭhapabbajitānaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "an5.88:2.3"
msgid "ñāto hoti yasassī sagahaṭṭhapabbajitānaṃ bahujanaparivāro; "
msgstr "They’re well-known, famous, with a large following that includes both laypeople and renunciates. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.88:2.4"
msgid "lābhī hoti cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārānaṃ; "
msgstr "They receive robes, alms-food, lodgings, and medicines and supplies for the sick. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
# NOTE: See BB’s note for variant.
#. VAR: appaṭividdhā → suppaṭividdhā (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "an5.88:2.5"
msgid "bahussuto hoti sutadharo sutasannicayo, ye te dhammā ādikalyāṇā majjhekalyāṇā pariyosānakalyāṇā sātthaṃ sabyañjanaṃ kevalaparipuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ abhivadanti, tathārūpāssa dhammā bahussutā honti dhātā vacasā paricitā manasānupekkhitā diṭṭhiyā appaṭividdhā; "
msgstr "They’re very learned, remembering and keeping what they’ve learned. These teachings are good in the beginning, good in the middle, and good in the end, meaningful and well-phrased, describing a spiritual practice that’s entirely full and pure. They are very learned in such teachings, remembering them, reinforcing them by recitation, mentally scrutinizing them, and understanding them with view. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.88:2.6"
msgid "micchādiṭṭhiko hoti viparītadassano, so bahujanaṃ saddhammā vuṭṭhāpetvā asaddhamme patiṭṭhāpeti. "
msgstr "But they have wrong view and distorted perspective. They draw many people away from the true teaching and establish them in false teachings. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.88:2.7"
msgid "Thero bhikkhu rattaññū cirapabbajito itipissa diṭṭhānugatiṃ āpajjanti, ñāto thero bhikkhu yasassī sagahaṭṭhapabbajitānaṃ bahujanaparivāro itipissa diṭṭhānugatiṃ āpajjanti, lābhī thero bhikkhu cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārānaṃ itipissa diṭṭhānugatiṃ āpajjanti, bahussuto thero bhikkhu sutadharo sutasannicayo itipissa diṭṭhānugatiṃ āpajjanti. "
msgstr "People follow their example, thinking that the senior mendicant is senior and has long gone forth. Or that they’re well-known, famous, with a large following that includes both laypeople and renunciates. Or that they receive robes, alms-food, lodgings, and medicines and supplies for the sick. Or that they’re very learned, remembering and keeping what they’ve learned. "

msgctxt "an5.88:2.8"
msgid "Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato thero bhikkhu bahujanaahitāya paṭipanno hoti bahujanaasukhāya bahuno janassa anatthāya ahitāya dukkhāya devamanussānaṃ. "
msgstr "A senior mendicant who has these five qualities is acting for the hurt and unhappiness of the people, for the harm, hurt, and suffering of gods and humans. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "an5.88:3.1"
msgid "Pañcahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato thero bhikkhu bahujanahitāya paṭipanno hoti bahujanasukhāya bahuno janassa atthāya hitāya sukhāya devamanussānaṃ. "
msgstr "A senior mendicant who has five qualities is acting for the welfare and happiness of the people, for the benefit, welfare, and happiness of gods and humans. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.116, sc4
msgctxt "an5.88:4.1"
msgid "Katamehi pañcahi? "
msgstr "What five? "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.88:4.2"
msgid "Thero hoti rattaññū cirapabbajito; "
msgstr "They are senior and have long gone forth. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.88:4.3"
msgid "ñāto hoti yasassī sagahaṭṭhapabbajitānaṃ bahujanaparivāro; "
msgstr "They’re well-known, famous, with a large following, including both laypeople and renunciates. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.88:4.4"
msgid "lābhī hoti cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārānaṃ; "
msgstr "They receive robes, alms-food, lodgings, and medicines and supplies for the sick. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.88:4.5"
msgid "bahussuto hoti sutadharo sutasannicayo, ye te dhammā ādikalyāṇā majjhekalyāṇā pariyosānakalyāṇā sātthaṃ sabyañjanaṃ kevalaparipuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ abhivadanti, tathārūpāssa dhammā bahussutā honti dhātā vacasā paricitā manasānupekkhitā diṭṭhiyā suppaṭividdhā; "
msgstr "They’re very learned, remembering and keeping what they’ve learned. These teachings are good in the beginning, good in the middle, and good in the end, meaningful and well-phrased, describing a spiritual practice that’s entirely full and pure. They are very learned in such teachings, remembering them, reinforcing them by recitation, mentally scrutinizing them, and comprehending them theoretically. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.88:4.6"
msgid "sammādiṭṭhiko hoti aviparītadassano, so bahujanaṃ asaddhammā vuṭṭhāpetvā saddhamme patiṭṭhāpeti. "
msgstr "And they have right view and an undistorted perspective. They draw many people away from false teachings and establish them in the true teaching. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.88:4.7"
msgid "Thero bhikkhu rattaññū cirapabbajito itipissa diṭṭhānugatiṃ āpajjanti, ñāto thero bhikkhu yasassī sagahaṭṭhapabbajitānaṃ bahujanaparivāro itipissa diṭṭhānugatiṃ āpajjanti, lābhī thero bhikkhu cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārānaṃ itipissa diṭṭhānugatiṃ āpajjanti, bahussuto thero bhikkhu sutadharo sutasannicayo itipissa diṭṭhānugatiṃ āpajjanti. "
msgstr "People follow their example, thinking that the senior mendicant is senior and has long gone forth. Or that they’re well-known, famous, with a large following that includes both laypeople and renunciates. Or that they receive robes, alms-food, lodgings, and medicines and supplies for the sick. Or that they’re very learned, remembering and keeping what they’ve learned. "

msgctxt "an5.88:4.8"
msgid "Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato thero bhikkhu bahujanahitāya paṭipanno hoti bahujanasukhāya bahuno janassa atthāya hitāya sukhāya devamanussānan”ti. "
msgstr "A senior mendicant who has these five qualities is acting for the welfare and happiness of the people, for the benefit, welfare, and happiness of gods and humans.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an5.88:4.9"
msgid "Aṭṭhamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

